column9: A primitive word; father, in a literal and immediate, or figurative and remote application) -- chief, (fore-)father(-less), X patrimony, principal. Compare names in \"Abi-\".

From (H6) 'abad; a perishing -- destruction. see HEBREW (H6) 'abad
From (H6) 'abad; a perishing -- destruction. see HEBREW (H6) 'abad

From (H75) 'abac; a manger or stall -- crib. see HEBREW (H75) 'abac

Contracted for (H141) 'Adoniyram; Adoram (or Adoniram), an Israelite -- Adoram. see HEBREW (H141) 'Adoniyram

column7: Adar is prince, an Assyr. idol, also a son of Sennacherib
column9: From (H142) 'adar and (H4428) melek; splendor of (the) king; Adrammelek, the name of an Assyrian idol, also of a son of Sennacherib -- Adrammelech. see HEBREW (H142) 'adar see HEBREW (H4428) melek
(Aramaic) an orthographical variation for (H1872) dra'; an arm, i.e. (figuratively) power -- force. see HEBREW (H1872) dra'

column7: a chief city of Bashan, also a place in Naphtali
column9: From the equivalent of (H153) edra'; mighty; Edrei, the name of two places in Palestine -- Edrei. see HEBREW (H153) edra'
Feminine of (H117) 'addiyr; something ample (as a large vine, a wide dress); also the same as (H145) 'eder -- garment, glory, goodly, mantle, robe. see HEBREW (H117) 'addiyr see HEBREW (H145) 'eder
A primitive root; to tread out (grain) -- thresh.
Or raheb {aw-habe'}; a primitive root; to have affection for (sexually or otherwise) -- (be-)love(-d, -ly, -r), like, friend.
From (H157) 'ahab; affection (in a good or a bad sense) -- love(-r). see HEBREW (H157) 'ahab
From (H156) 'adash; meaning the same as (H158) 'ahab -- love. see HEBREW (H156) 'adash see HEBREW (H158) 'ahab
Feminine of (H158) 'ahab and meaning the same -- love. see HEBREW (H158) 'ahab
From an unused root meaning to be united; unity; Ohad, an Israelite -- Ohad.
Apparently a primitive word expressing pain exclamatorily; Oh! -- ah, alas.

column7: a place and a stream in Babylon
column9: Probably of foreign origin; Ahava, a river of Babylonia -- Ahava.
From the same as (H161) 'Ohad; united; Ehud, the name of two or three Israelites -- Ehud. see HEBREW (H161) 'Ohad

Apparently an orthographical variation for (H346) 'ayeh; where -- I will be (Hos. 13:10, Hos. 13:14) (which is often the rendering of the same Hebrew form from (H1961) hayah). see HEBREW (H346) 'ayeh see HEBREW (H1961) hayah
A primitive root; to be clear -- shine.

column7: to move a tent (from place to place)
column9: A denominative from (H168) 'ohel; to tent -- pitch (remove) a tent. see HEBREW (H168) 'ohel
From (H166) 'ahal; a tent (as clearly conspicuous from a distance) -- covering, (dwelling)(place), home, tabernacle, tent. see HEBREW (H166) 'ahal
The same as (H168) 'ohel; Ohel, an Israelite -- Ohel. see HEBREW (H168) 'ohel

column7: she who has a tent, a symbolic name for Samaria
column9: In form a feminine of (H168) 'ohel, but in fact for.Oholahh {o-hol-aw'}; from (H168) 'ohel; her tent (i.e. Idolatrous sanctuary); Oholah, a symbol. Name for Samaria -- Aholah. see HEBREW (H168) 'ohel see HEBREW (H168) 'ohel

column7: father\'s tent, an assistant of Bezalel
column9: From (H168) 'ohel and (H1) 'ab; tent of (his) father; Oholiab, an Israelite -- Aholiab. see HEBREW (H168) 'ohel see HEBREW (H1) 'ab

column7: tent in her, a symbolic name for Jer
column9: (similarly with (H170) 'Oholah) for hoholiybahh {o''-hol-e-baw'}; from (H168) 'ohel; my tent (is) in her; Oholibah, a symbolic name for Judah -- Aholibah. see HEBREW (H170) 'Oholah see HEBREW (H168) 'ohel

column7: tent of the high place, wife of Esau, also an Edomite leader
column9: From (H168) 'ohel and (H1116) bamah; tent of (the) height; Oholibamah, a wife of Esau -- Aholibamah. see HEBREW (H168) 'ohel see HEBREW (H1116) bamah
Or (feminine) ahalowth {a-haw-loth'} (only used thus in the plural); of foreign origin; aloe wood (i.e. Sticks) -- (tree of lign-) aloes.
Of uncertain derivation; Aharon, the brother of Moses -- Aaron.

column8: also, and, either, if, at the least, nor, or, otherwise,
column9: Presumed to be the \"constructive\" or genitival form of -av {av}; short for (H185) 'avvah; desire (and so probably in Prov. 31:4); hence (by way of alternative) or, also if -- also, and, either, if, at the least, X nor, or, otherwise, then, whether. see HEBREW (H185) 'avvah
From (H176) 'ow and (H410) 'el; wish of God; Uel, and Israelite -- Uel. see HEBREW (H176) 'ow see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: a bottle (made from animal skin), a necromancer
column9: From the same as (H1) 'ab (apparently through the idea of prattling a father's name); properly, a mumble, i.e. A water skin (from its hollow sound); hence a necromancer (ventriloquist, as from a jar) -- bottle, familiar spirit. see HEBREW (H1) 'ab
Probably from (H56) 'abal; mournful; Obil, an Ishmaelite -- Obil. see HEBREW (H56) 'abal
Or (shortened) ubal {oo-bawl'}; from (H2986) yabal (in the sense of (H2988) yabal); a stream -- river. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal see HEBREW (H2988) yabal
From an unused root meaning to rake together; a poker (for turning or gathering embers) -- (fire-)brand.
Or (shortened) rodowth {o-doth'} (only thus in the plural); from the same as (H181) 'uwd; turnings (i.e. Occasions); (adverb) on account of -- (be-)cause, concerning, sake. see HEBREW (H181) 'uwd

column8: covet, greatly desire, be desirous, long, lust after
column9: A primitive root; to wish for -- covet, (greatly) desire, be desirous, long, lust (after).

column7: to sign, mark, describe with a mark
column9: A primitive root; to extend or mark out -- point out.
From (H183) 'avah; longing -- desire, lust after, pleasure. see HEBREW (H183) 'avah
Perhaps by permutation for (H5813) Uzziy, strong; Uzai, an Israelite -- Uzai. see HEBREW (H5813) Uzziy

column7: a son of Joktan, also his desc., also a place of unc. location
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Uzal, a son of Joktan -- Uzal.
Probably from (H183) 'avah (in the sense of crying out after); lamentation; also interjectionally Oh! -- alas, woe. see HEBREW (H183) 'avah

column7: one of five chiefs of Midian
column9: Probably from (H183) 'avah; desirous; Evi, a Midianitish chief -- Evi. see HEBREW (H183) 'avah
Feminine of (H188) 'owy -- woe. see HEBREW (H188) 'owy
From an unused root (meaning to be perverse); (figuratively) silly -- fool(-ish) (man).

column7: man of Merodach, son and successor of Nebuchadnezzar
column9: Of Aramaic derivation and probably meaning soldier of Merodak; Evil-Merodak, a Babylonian king -- Evil-merodach.
From an unused root meaning to twist, i.e. (by implication) be strong; the body (as being rolled together); also powerful -- mighty, strength.

column8: if so be, may be, peradventure, unless
column9: Or (shortened) rulay {oo-lah'ee}; from (H176) 'ow; if not; hence perhaps -- if so be, may be, peradventure, unless. see HEBREW (H176) 'ow
Of Persian derivation; the Ulai (or Eulaeus), a river of Persia -- Ulai.
From (H191) 'eviyl; silly, foolish; hence (morally) impious -- foolish. see HEBREW (H191) 'eviyl
Or (shortened),ulam {oo-lawm'}; from (H481) 'alam (in the sense of tying); a vestibule (as bound to the building) -- porch. see HEBREW (H481) 'alam
Appar, from (H481) 'alam (in the sense of dumbness); solitary; Ulam, the name of two Israelites -- Ulam. see HEBREW (H481) 'alam

column8: as for, but, howbeit, in very deed, surely, truly, wherefore
column9: Apparently a variation of (H194) 'uwlay; however or on the contrary -- as for, but, howbeit, in very deed, surely, truly, wherefore. see HEBREW (H194) 'uwlay
From the same as (H191) 'eviyl; silliness -- folly, foolishly(-ness). see HEBREW (H191) 'eviyl
From (H559) 'amar; talkative; Omar, a grandson of Esau -- Omar. see HEBREW (H559) 'amar
Probably from the same as (H205) 'aven (in the sense of effort, but successful); ability, power, (figuratively) wealth -- force, goods, might, strength, substance. see HEBREW (H205) 'aven

column7: a chief of the tribe of Reuben
column9: The same as (H202) 'own; On, an Israelite -- On. see HEBREW (H202) 'own
Or (shortened); On {one}; of Egyptian derivation; On, a city of Egypt -- On.

column8: affliction, evil, false, idol, iniquity, mischief, mourner, naught,
column9: From an unused root perhaps meaning properly, to pant (hence, to exert oneself, usually in vain; to come to naught); strictly nothingness; also trouble. Vanity, wickedness; specifically an idol -- affliction, evil, false, idol, iniquity, mischief, mourners(-ing), naught, sorrow, unjust, unrighteous, vain,vanity, wicked(-ness). Compare (H369) 'ayin. see HEBREW (H369) 'ayin

column7: wickedness, a contemptuous synonym for two places
column9: The same as (H205) 'aven; idolatry; Aven, the contemptuous synonym of three places, one in Coele-Syria, one in Egypt (On), and one in Palestine (Bethel) -- Aven. See also (H204) 'Own, (H1007) Beyth 'Aven. see HEBREW (H205) 'aven see HEBREW (H204) 'Own see HEBREW (H1007) Beyth 'Aven
Or (shortened);Onow {o-no'}; prolonged from (H202) 'own; strong; Ono, a place in Palestine -- Ono. see HEBREW (H202) 'own

column7: vigorous, the name of an Edomite and of an Israelite
column9: A variation of (H209) 'Ownan; strong; Onam, the name of an Edomite and of an Israelite -- Onam. see HEBREW (H209) 'Ownan
A variation of (H207) 'Ownow; strong; Onan, a son of Judah -- Onan. see HEBREW (H207) 'Ownow

column7: a region where gold is found
column9: Perhaps a corruption of (H211) 'Owphiyr; Uphaz, a famous gold region -- Uphaz. see HEBREW (H211) 'Owphiyr

column7: a son of Joktan, also his desc., also a region from which gold comes
column9: Or (shortened) pophiyr {o-feer'}; and fowphir {o- feer'}; of uncertain derivation; Ophir, the name of a son of Joktan, and of a gold region in the East -- Ophir.
Or (shortened) pophan {o-fawn'}; from an unused root meaning to revolve; a wheel -- wheel.

column7: to press, be pressed, make haste
column9: A primitive root; to press; (by implication) to be close, hurry, withdraw -- (make) haste(-n, -y), labor, be narrow.
From (H686) 'atsar; a depository -- armory, cellar, garner, store(-house), treasure(-house) (-y). see HEBREW (H686) 'atsar

column8: break give, show light en set on fire, shine
column9: A primitive root; to be (causative, make) luminous (literally and metaphorically) -- X break of day, glorious, kindle, (be, en-, give, show) light (-en, -ened), set on fire, shine.

column8: bright, clear, day, lightning, morning, sun
column9: From (H215) 'owr; illumination or (concrete) luminary (in every sense, including lightning, happiness, etc.) -- bright, clear, + day, light (-ning), morning, sun. see HEBREW (H215) 'owr
From (H215) 'owr; flame; hence (in the plural) the East (as being the region of light) -- fire, light. See also (H224) 'Uwriym. see HEBREW (H215) 'owr see HEBREW (H224) 'Uwriym
The same as (H217) 'uwr; Ur, a place in Chaldaea; also an Israelite -- Ur. see HEBREW (H217) 'uwr
Feminine of (H216) 'owr; luminousness, i.e. (figuratively) prosperity; also a plant (as being bright) -- herb, light. see HEBREW (H216) 'owr
By transposition for (H723) 'urvah; a stall -- cote. see HEBREW (H723) 'urvah
From (H217) 'uwr; fiery; Uri, the name of three Israelites -- Uri. see HEBREW (H217) 'uwr
From (H217) 'uwr and (H410) 'el; flame of God; Uriel, the name of two Israelites -- Uriel. see HEBREW (H217) 'uwr see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: flame of Yah, the name of a Hittite and of two Israelites
column9: Or (prolonged) Uwriyahuw {oo-ree-yaw'-hoo}; from (H217) 'uwr and (H3050) Yahh; flame of Jah; Urijah, the name of one Hittite and five Israelites -- Uriah, Urijah. see HEBREW (H217) 'uwr see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: part of the high priest\'s breastplate
column9: Plur of (H217) 'uwr; lights; Urim, the oracular brilliancy of the figures in the high-priest's breastplate -- Urim. see HEBREW (H217) 'uwr
A primitive root; properly, to come, i.e. (implied) to assent -- consent.

Probably from (H225) 'uwth (in the sense of appearing); a signal (literally or figuratively), as a flag, beacon, monument, omen, prodigy, evidence, etc. -- mark, miracle, (en-)sign, token. see HEBREW (H225) 'uwth

column8: beginning, for, from, hitherto, now, of old, once, since,
column9: A demonstrative adverb; at that time or place; also as a conjunction, therefore -- beginning, for, from, hitherto, now, of old, once, since, then, at which time, yet.
(Aramaic) or iazah (Aramaic) {az-aw'}; to kindle; (by implication) to heat -- heat, hot.

column7: the father of one of David\'s men
column9: Probably from (H231) 'ezowb; hyssop-like; Ezbai, an Israelite -- Ezbai. see HEBREW (H231) 'ezowb
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; firm -- be gone.
Probably of foreign derivation; hyssop -- hyssop.
From (H246) 'aziqqiym; something girt; a belt, also a band -- girdle. see HEBREW (H246) 'aziqqiym
Probably from (H227) 'az; at that time -- then. see HEBREW (H227) 'az
From (H2142) zakar; a reminder; specifically remembrance- offering -- memorial. see HEBREW (H2142) zakar

column8: fail, gad about, go to and fro but in Ezek
column9: A primitive root; to go away, hence, to disappear -- fail, gad about, go to and fro (but in Ezek. 27:19 the word is rendered by many \"from Uzal,\" by others \"yarn\"), be gone (spent).
(Aramaic) the same as (H235) 'azal; to depart -- go (up). see HEBREW (H235) 'azal
From (H235) 'azal; departure; Ezel, a memorial stone in Palestine -- Ezel. see HEBREW (H235) 'azal

column8: give perceive by the ear, hearken
column9: A primitive root; probably to expand; but used only as a denominative from (H241) 'ozen; to broaden out the ear (with the hand), i.e. (by implication) to listen -- give (perceive by the) ear, hear(-ken). See (H239) 'azan. see HEBREW (H241) 'ozen see HEBREW (H239) 'azan
A primitive root (rather identical with (H238) 'azan through the idea of scales as if two ears); to weigh, i.e. (figuratively) ponder -- give good head. see HEBREW (H238) 'azan
From (H238) 'azan; a spade or paddle (as having a broad end) -- weapon. see HEBREW (H238) 'azan

column8: advertise, audience, displease, ear, hearing, show
column9: From (H238) 'azan; broadness. I.e. (concrete) the ear (from its form in man) -- + advertise, audience, + displease, ear, hearing, + show. see HEBREW (H238) 'azan

column7: portion of Sheerah, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H238) 'azan and (H7609) She'erah; plat of Sheerah (i.e. Settled by him); Uzzen-Sheerah, a place in Palestine -- Uzzen-sherah. see HEBREW (H238) 'azan see HEBREW (H7609) She'erah
From (H238) 'azan and (H8396) Tabowr; flats (i.e. Tops) of Tabor (i.e. Situated on it); Aznoth-Tabor, a place in Palestine -- Aznoth-tabor. see HEBREW (H238) 'azan see HEBREW (H8396) Tabowr

column7: my hearing, a son of Gad
column9: From (H241) 'ozen; having (quick) ears; Ozni, an Israelite; also an Oznite (collectively), his descendant -- Ozni, Oznites. see HEBREW (H241) 'ozen
From (H238) 'azan and (H3050) Yahh; heard by Jah; Azanjah, an Israelite -- Azaniah. see HEBREW (H238) 'azan see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A variation for (H2131) ziyqah; manacles -- chains. see HEBREW (H2131) ziyqah

column8: bind compass about, gird up, with
column9: A primitive root; to belt -- bind (compass) about, gird (up, with).
A variation for (H2220) zrowa'; the arm -- arm. see HEBREW (H2220) zrowa'

column8: bay tree, homeborn in the land, of the one\'s own country nation
column9: From (H2224) zarach (in the sense of springing up); a spontaneous growth, i.e. Native (tree or persons) -- bay tree, (home-)born (in the land), of the (one's own) country (nation). see HEBREW (H2224) zarach
Patronymic from (H2246) Chobab; an Ezrachite or descendant of Zerach -- Ezrahite. see HEBREW (H2246) Chobab

A primitive word; a brother (used in the widest sense of literal relationship and metaphorical affinity or resemblance (like (H1) 'ab)) -- another, brother(-ly); kindred, like, other. Compare also the proper names beginning with \"Ah-\" or \"Ahi-\". see HEBREW (H1) 'ab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H251) 'ach -- brother. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach
A variation for (H162) 'ahahh; Oh! (expressive of grief or surprise) -- ah, alas. see HEBREW (H162) 'ahahh
Of uncertain derivation; a fire-pot or chafing dish -- hearth.
Probably from (H253) 'ach; a howler or lonesome wild animal -- doleful creature. see HEBREW (H253) 'ach

column7: father\'s brother, a king of Isr., also a false prophet
column9: Once (by contraction) oechab (Jer. 29:22) {ekh- awb'}; from (H251) 'ach and (H1) 'ab; brother (i.e. Friend) of (his) father; Achab, the name of a king of Israel and of a prophet at Babylon -- Ahab. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H1) 'ab

column7: brother of an intelligent one, an Israelite
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H995) biyn; brother (i.e. Possessor) of understanding; Achban, an Israelite -- Ahban. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H995) biyn
Perhaps a primitive root; to unify, i.e. (figuratively) collect (one's thoughts) -- go one way or other.

column8: a, alike, alone, altogether, and, anything, apiece, a certain
column9: A numeral from (H258) 'achad; properly, united, i.e. One; or (as an ordinal) first -- a, alike, alone, altogether, and, any(-thing), apiece, a certain, (dai-)ly, each (one), + eleven, every, few, first, + highway, a man, once, one, only, other, some, together, see HEBREW (H258) 'achad
Of uncertain (perhaps Egyptian) derivation; a bulrush or any marshy grass (particularly that along the Nile) -- flag, meadow.
From (H258) 'achad; united; Echud, the name of three Israelites -- Ehud. see HEBREW (H258) 'achad
From (H2331) chavah (in the sense of (H2324) chava'); an utterance -- declaration. see HEBREW (H2331) chavah see HEBREW (H2324) chava'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H262) 'achvah; solution (of riddles) -- showing. see HEBREW (H262) 'achvah
From (H251) 'ach; fraternity -- brotherhood. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach
By reduplication from (H251) 'ach; brotherly; Achoach, an Israelite -- Ahoah. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach
Patronymic from (H264) 'achavah; an Achochite or descendant of Achoach -- Ahohite. see HEBREW (H264) 'achavah
Perhaps from (H251) 'ach and (H4325) mayim; brother (i.e. Neighbour) of water; Achumai, an Israelite -- Ahumai. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H4325) mayim

column8: afterward, back part hereafter, hinder part, time to come, without
column9: Or (shortened) achor {aw-khore'}; from (H299) Achiyra'; the hinder part; hence (adverb) behind, backward; also (as facing north) the West -- after(-ward), back (part, -side, -ward), hereafter, (be-)hind(-er part), time to come, without. see HEBREW (H299) Achiyra'
Irregular feminine of (H251) 'ach; a sister (used very widely (like (H250) 'Ezrachiy), literally and figuratively) -- (an-)other, sister, together. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H250) 'Ezrachiy

column7: to grasp, take hold, take possession
column8: be affrighted, bar, catch, lay, take hold back, come upon, fasten, handle,
column9: A primitive root; to seize (often with the accessory idea of holding in possession) -- + be affrighted, bar, (catch, lay, take) hold (back), come upon, fasten, handle, portion, (get, have or take) possess(-ion).
From (H270) 'achaz; possessor; Achaz, the name of a Jewish king and of an Israelite -- Ahaz. see HEBREW (H270) 'achaz
Feminine passive participle from (H270) 'achaz; something seized, i.e. A possession (especially of land) -- possession. see HEBREW (H270) 'achaz

column7: Yah has grasped, an Israelite name
column9: From (H270) 'achaz; seizer; Achzai, an Israelite -- Ahasai. see HEBREW (H270) 'achaz

column7: Yah has grasped, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or (prolonged) rachazyahuw {akh-az-yaw'-hoo}; from (H270) 'achaz and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has seized; Achazjah, the name of a Jewish and an Israelite king -- Ahaziah. see HEBREW (H270) 'achaz see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H270) 'achaz; seizure; Achuzzam, an Israelite -- Ahuzam. see HEBREW (H270) 'achaz
A variation of (H272) 'achuzzah; possession; Achuzzath, a Philistine -- Ahuzzath. see HEBREW (H272) 'achuzzah

column7: brother of Yah, an Israelite name
column9: From (H251) 'ach; brotherly; Achi, the name of two Israelites -- Ahi. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach
Probably the same as (H277) 'Achiy; Echi, an Israelite -- Ehi. see HEBREW (H277) 'Achiy

column7: brother of mother, one of David\'s men
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H517) 'em; brother of the mother (i.e. Uncle); Achiam, an Israelite -- Ahiam. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H517) 'em
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2420) chiydah, an enigma -- hard sentence. see HEBREW (H2420) chiydah

column7: brother of Yah, an Israelite name
column9: Or (prolonged) pachiyahuw {akh-ee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H251) 'ach and (H3050) Yahh; brother (i.e. Worshipper) of Jah; Achijah, the name of nine Israelites -- Ahiah, Ahijah. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: brother of majesty, a leader of Asher
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H1935) howd; brother (i.e. Possessor) of renown; Achihud, an Israelite -- Ahihud. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H1935) howd

column7: brotherly, the name of several Israelites
column9: Prolonged from (H251) 'ach; brotherly; Achio, the name of three Israelites -- Ahio. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach

column7: brother of a riddle, a Benjamite
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H2330) chuwd; brother of a riddle (i.e. Mysterious); Achichud, an Israelite -- Ahihud. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H2330) chuwd

column7: my brother is goodness, two Israelites
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H2898) tuwb; brother of goodness; Achitub, the name of several priests -- Ahitub. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H2898) tuwb
From (H251) 'ach and (H3205) yalad; brother of one born; Achilud, an Israelite -- Ahilud. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H3205) yalad

column7: my brother is death, a Levite
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H4191) muwth; brother of death; Achimoth, an Israelite -- Ahimoth. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H4191) muwth

column7: brother of a king, an Israelite name, also a Hittite name
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H4428) melek; brother of (the) king; Achimelek, the name of an Israelite and of a Hittite -- Ahimelech. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H4428) melek

column7: a Levite, also a son of Anak
column9: Or machiyman {akh-ee-mawn'}; from (H251) 'ach and (H4480) min; brother of a portion (i.e. Gift); Achiman, the name of an Anakite and of an Israelite -- Ahiman. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H4480) min

column7: my brother is wrath, two Israelites
column9: From (H251) 'ach and the equivalent of (H4619) Ma'ats; brother of anger; Achimaats, the name of three Israelites -- Ahimaaz. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H4619) Ma'ats
From (H251) 'ach; brotherly; Achjan, an Israelite -- Ahian. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach

column7: my brother is noble, an official of Solomon
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H5068) nadab; brother of liberality; Achinadab, an Israelite -- Ahinadab. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H5068) nadab

column7: my brother is delight, two Israelite women
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H5278) no'am; brother of pleasantness; Achinoam, the name of two Israelitesses -- Ahinoam. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H5278) no'am

column7: my brother has supported, an Israelite
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H5564) camak; brother of support; Achisamak, an Israelite -- Ahisamach. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H5564) camak

column7: my brother is help, two Israelites
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H5828) ezer; brother of help; Achiezer, the name of two Israelites -- Ahiezer. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H5828) ezer

column7: my brother has arisen, an Israelite
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H6965) quwm; brother of rising (i.e. High); Achikam, an Israelite -- Ahikam. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H6965) quwm

column7: brother of (the) lofty, a son of Benjamin
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H7311) ruwm; brother of height (i.e. High); Achiram, an Israelite -- Ahiram. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm
Patronymic from (H297) 'Achiyram; an Achiramite or descendant (collectively) of Achiram -- Ahiramites. see HEBREW (H297) 'Achiyram

column7: my brother is evil, a leader of Naphtali
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H7451) ra'; brother of wrong; Achira, an Israelite -- Ahira. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H7451) ra'
From (H251) 'ach and (H7837) shachar; brother of (the) dawn; Achishachar, an Israelite -- Ahishar. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H7837) shachar

column7: my brother has sung, one of Solomon\'s officials
column9: From (H251) 'ach and (H7891) shiyr; brother of (the) singer; Achishar, an Israelite -- Ahishar. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H7891) shiyr
From (H251) 'ach and (H8602) taphel; brother of folly; Achithophel, an Israelite -- Ahithophel. see HEBREW (H251) 'ach see HEBREW (H8602) taphel
From the same root as (H2459) cheleb; fatness (i.e. Fertile); Achlab, a place in Palestine -- Ahlab. see HEBREW (H2459) cheleb
The same as (H305) 'achalay; wishful; Achlai, the name of an Israelitess and of an Israelite -- Ahlai. see HEBREW (H305) 'achalay
Or achaley {akh-al-ay'}; prob from (H253) 'ach and a variation of (H3863) luw'; would that! -- O that, would God. see HEBREW (H253) 'ach see HEBREW (H3863) luw'
Perhaps from (H2492) chalam (and thus dream-stone); a gem, probably the amethyst -- amethyst. see HEBREW (H2492) chalam
Of Persian derivation; Achmetha (i.e. Ecbatana), the summer capital of Persia -- Achmetha.
Of uncertain derivation; Achasbai, an Israelite -- Ahasbai.

column8: continue, defer, delay, hinder, be late slack, stay there, tarry longer
column9: A primitive root; to loiter (i.e. Be behind); by implication to procrastinate -- continue, defer, delay, hinder, be late (slack), stay (there), tarry (longer).

column8: after that again, at, away from, back from behind, beside, by
column9: From (H309) 'achar; properly, the hind part; generally used as an adverb or conjunction, after (in various senses) -- after (that, -ward), again, at, away from, back (from, -side), behind, beside, by, follow (after, -ing), forasmuch, from, hereafter, hinder end, + out (over) live, + persecute, posterity, pursuing, remnant, seeing, since, thence(-forth), when, with. see HEBREW (H309) 'achar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H310) 'achar; after -- (here-)after. see HEBREW (H310) 'achar
From (H309) 'achar; properly, hinder; generally, next, other, etc. -- (an-)other man, following, next, strange. see HEBREW (H309) 'achar
The same as (H312) 'acher; Acher, an Israelite -- Aher. see HEBREW (H312) 'acher

column8: afterward, to come, following, hinder last, latter, reward
column9: Or (shortened);acharon {akh-ar-one'}; from (H309) 'achar; hinder; generally, late or last; specifically (as facing the east) western -- after (-ward), to come, following, hind(-er, -ermost, -most), last, latter, rereward, ut(ter)most. see HEBREW (H309) 'achar
From (H310) 'achar and (H251) 'ach; after (his) brother: Achrach, an Israelite -- Aharah. see HEBREW (H310) 'achar see HEBREW (H251) 'ach
From (H310) 'achar and (H2426) cheyl; behind (the) intrenchment (i.e. Safe); Acharchel, an Israelite -- Aharhel, see HEBREW (H310) 'achar see HEBREW (H2426) cheyl
(Aramaic) from (H311) 'achar; other -- (an-)other. see HEBREW (H311) 'achar
(Aramaic) or (shortened):ochoren (Aramaic) {okh-or-ane'}; from (H317) 'ochoriy; last -- at last. see HEBREW (H317) 'ochoriy

column8: last, latter end time, hinder, uttermost, length, posterity, remnant, residue, reward
column9: From (H310) 'achar; the last or end, hence, the future; also posterity -- (last, latter) end (time), hinder (utter) -most, length, posterity, remnant, residue, reward. see HEBREW (H310) 'achar
(Aramaic) from (H311) 'achar; the same as (H319) 'achariyth; later -- latter. see HEBREW (H311) 'achar see HEBREW (H319) 'achariyth
(Aramaic) from (H311) 'achar; the same as (H317) 'ochoriy; other -- (an-)other. see HEBREW (H311) 'achar see HEBREW (H317) 'ochoriy
Prolonged from (H268) 'achowr; backwards -- back (-ward, again). see HEBREW (H268) 'achowr
Of Persian derivation; a satrap or governor of a main province (of Persia) -- lieutenant.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H323) 'achashdarpan -- prince. see HEBREW (H323) 'achashdarpan

Or (shortened) pachashrosh {akh- ash-rosh'} (Esth. 10:1); of Persian origin; Achashverosh (i.e. Ahasuerus or Artaxerxes, but in this case Xerxes), the title (rather than name) of a Persian king -- Ahasuerus.

column7: belonging to the realm, an Israelite
column9: Probably of Persian derivation; an achastarite (i.e. Courier); the designation (rather than name) of an Israelite -- Haakashtari (includ. The article).
Of Persian origin; a mule -- camel.
From an unused root perhaps meaning to move softly; (as a noun) a necromancer (from their soft incantations), (as an adverb) gently -- charmer, gently, secret, softly.

column7: a bramble, buckthorn, also a city in Canaan
column9: From an unused root probably meaning to pierce or make fast; a thorn-tree (especially the buckthorn) -- Atad, bramble, thorn.
From an unused root (probably meaning to bind); properly, twisted (yarn), i.e. Tapestry -- fine linen.
A primitive root; to close (the lips or ears); by analology to contract (a window by bevelled jambs) -- narrow, shut, stop.
A primitive root; to close up -- shut.
From (H332) 'atar; maimed; Ater, the name of three Israelites -- Ater. see HEBREW (H332) 'atar
From (H332) 'atar; shut up, i.e. Impeded (as to the use of the right hand) -- + left-handed. see HEBREW (H332) 'atar

column8: how, what, whence, where, whether, which way
column9: Perhaps from (H370) 'aiyn; where? Hence how? -- how, what, whence, where, whether, which (way). see HEBREW (H370) 'aiyn
Probably identical with (H335) 'ay (through the idea of a query); not -- island (Job 22:30). see HEBREW (H335) 'ay
Short from (H188) 'owy; alas! -- woe. see HEBREW (H188) 'owy
Probably identical with (H337) 'iy (through the idea of a doleful sound); a howler (used only in the plural), i.e. Any solitary wild creature; --wild beast of the islands. see HEBREW (H337) 'iy
From (H183) 'avah; properly, a habitable spot (as desirable); dry land, a coast, an island -- country, isle, island. see HEBREW (H183) 'avah
A primitive root; to hate (as one of an opposite tribe or party); hence to be hostile -- be an enemy.
Or (fully) owyeb {o-yabe'}; active participle of (H340) 'ayab; hating; an adversary -- enemy, foe. see HEBREW (H340) 'ayab
From (H340) 'ayab; hostility -- emnity, hatred. see HEBREW (H340) 'ayab
From the same as (H181) 'uwd (in the sense of bending down); oppression; by implication misfortune, ruin -- calamity, destruction. see HEBREW (H181) 'uwd
Perhaps from (H337) 'iy; the screamer, i.e. A hawk -- kite, vulture. see HEBREW (H337) 'iy

column7: falcon, the name of a Horite, also of an Israelite
column9: The same as (H344) 'ayah; Ajah, the name of two Israelites -- Aiah, Ajah. see HEBREW (H344) 'ayah
Prolonged from (H335) 'ay; where? -- where. see HEBREW (H335) 'ay
From (H340) 'ayab; hated (i.e. Persecuted); Ijob, the patriarch famous for his patience -- Job. see HEBREW (H340) 'ayab

column7: queen of Israel with King Ahab
column9: From (H336) 'iy and (H2083) Zbul; Izebel, the wife of king Ahab -- Jezebel. see HEBREW (H336) 'iy see HEBREW (H2083) Zbul
Also eykah {ay-kaw'}; and teykakah {ay-kaw'-kah}; prolonged from (H335) 'ay; how? Or how!; also where -- how, what. see HEBREW (H335) 'ay
From (H336) 'iy and (H3519) kabowd; (there is) no glory, i.e. Inglorious; Ikabod, a son of Phineas -- I-chabod. see HEBREW (H336) 'iy see HEBREW (H3519) kabowd
Probably a variation for (H349) 'eyk, but not as an interogative; where -- where. see HEBREW (H349) 'eyk

column8: mighty man, lintel, oak, post, ram, tree
column9: From the same as (H193) 'uwl; properly, strength; hence, anything strong; specifically a chief (politically); also a ram (from his strength); a pilaster (as a strong support); an oak or other strong tree -- mighty (man), lintel, oak, post, ram, tree. see HEBREW (H193) 'uwl
A variation of (H352) 'ayil; strength -- strength. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil
An intensive form of (H352) 'ayil (in the sense of ram); a stag or male deer -- hart. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil
Feminine of (H354) 'ayal; a doe or female deer -- hind. see HEBREW (H354) 'ayal

column7: terebinth, an Israelite name, also a Hittite, also a city in Dan
column9: Or (shortened);Elown {ay-lone'}; or Eylon {ay- lone'}; from (H352) 'ayil; oak-grove; Elon, the name of a place in Palestine, and also of one Hittite, two Israelites -- Elon. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil

column7: deer, the name of several cities in Palestine
column9: From (H354) 'ayal; deer-field; Ajalon, the name of five places in Palestine -- Aijalon, Ajalon. see HEBREW (H354) 'ayal

column7: terebinth of (the) house of favor, a place in Dan
column9: From (H356) 'Eylown, (H1004) bayith, and (H2603) chanan; oak-grove of (the) house of favor; Elon of Beth-chanan, a place in Palestine -- Elon-beth-hanan. see HEBREW (H356) 'Eylown see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H2603) chanan
Or meylath {ay-lath'}; from (H352) 'ayil; trees or a grove (i.e. Palms); Eloth or Elath, a place on the Red Sea -- Elath, Eloth. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil
Feminine of (H353) 'eyal; power; by implication, protection -- strength. see HEBREW (H353) 'eyal
Or (shortened);elam {ay-lawm'}; or (feminine) ielammah {ay-lam-maw'}; probably from (H352) 'ayil; a pillar-space (or colonnade), i.e. A pale (or portico) -- arch. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil

column7: terebinths, a place in the desert
column9: Plural of (H352) 'ayil; palm-trees; Elim, a place in the Desert -- Elim. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H356) 'Eylown; a tree -- tree. see HEBREW (H356) 'Eylown

column7: terebinth of Paran, a city and harbor on the Red Sea
column9: From (H352) 'ayil and (H6290) Pa'ran; oak of Paran; El- Paran, a portion of the district of Paran -- El-paran. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil see HEBREW (H6290) Pa'ran

column7: lofty tree, a city and harbor on the Red Sea
column9: The same as (H355) 'ayalah; a doe -- hind, Aijeleth. see HEBREW (H355) 'ayalah
From an unused root (meaning to frighten); frightful -- terrible.

column8: dread, fear, horror, idol, terrible, terror
column9: Or (shortened) remah {ay-maw'}; from the same as (H366) 'ayom; fright; concrete, an idol (as a bugbear) -- dread, fear, horror, idol, terrible, terror. see HEBREW (H366) 'ayom
Plural of (H367) 'eymah; terrors; Emim, an early Canaanitish (or Maobitish) tribe -- Emims. see HEBREW (H367) 'eymah

column8: else, except, fail, fatherless, be gone, incurable, neither, never,
column9: As if from a primitive root meaning to be nothing or not exist; a non-entity; generally used as a negative particle -- else, except, fail, (father-)less, be gone, in(-curable), neither, never, no (where), none, nor, (any, thing), not, nothing, to nought, past, un(-searchable), well-nigh, without. Compare (H370) 'aiyn. see HEBREW (H370) 'aiyn

Probably identical with (H369) 'ayin in the sense of query (compare (H336) 'iy); --where? (only in connection with prepositional prefix, whence) -- whence, where. see HEBREW (H369) 'ayin see HEBREW (H336) 'iy
Apparently a shortened form of (H369) 'ayin; but (like (H370) 'aiyn) an interrogative: is it not? -- not. see HEBREW (H369) 'ayin see HEBREW (H370) 'aiyn
From (H336) 'iy and (H5828) ezer; helpless; Iezer, an Israelite -- Jeezer. see HEBREW (H336) 'iy see HEBREW (H5828) ezer
Patronymic from (H372) Iy'ezer; an Iezrite or descendant of Iezer -- Jezerite. see HEBREW (H372) Iy'ezer
Or (shortened) ephah {ay-faw'}; of Egyptian derivation; an ephah or measure for grain; hence, a measure in general -- ephah, (divers) measure(-s).
From (H335) 'ay and (H6311) poh; what place?; also (of time) when?; or (of means) how?; --what manner, where. see HEBREW (H335) 'ay see HEBREW (H6311) poh

column8: great, mighty man, he, high degree, him that is, husband, mankind,
column9: Contracted for (H582) 'enowsh (or perhaps rather from an unused root meaning to be extant); a man as an individual or a male person; often used as an adjunct to a more definite term (and in such cases frequently not expressed in translation) -- also, another, any (man), a certain, + champion, consent, each, every (one), fellow, (foot-, husband-)man, (good-, great, mighty) man, he, high (degree), him (that is), husband, man(-kind), + none, one, people, person, + steward, what (man) soever, whoso(-ever), worthy. Compare (H802) 'ishshah. see HEBREW (H582) 'enowsh see HEBREW (H802) 'ishshah
Denominative from (H376) 'iysh; to be a man, i.e. Act in a manly way -- show (one) self a man. see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh

column7: man of shame, a son of Saul and king of Isr
column9: From (H376) 'iysh and (H1322) bosheth; man of shame; Ish- Bosheth, a son of King Saul -- Ish-bosheth. see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh see HEBREW (H1322) bosheth

column7: man of majesty, a man of Manasseh
column9: From (H376) 'iysh and (H1935) howd; man of renown; Ishod, an Israelite -- Ishod. see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh see HEBREW (H1935) howd

column8: apple of the eye, black, obscure
column9: Diminutive from (H376) 'iysh; the little man of the eye; the pupil or ball; hence, the middle (of night) -- apple (of the eye), black, obscure. see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh

column7: Ish-chail, an Israelite -- a valiant man
column8: Ish-chail, an Israelite -- a valiant man
column9: From (H376) 'iysh and (H2428) chayil; man of might; by defect. Transcription (2 Sam. 23:20) Iysh-Chay {eesh-khah'ee}; as if from (H376) 'iysh and (H2416) chay; living man; Ish-chail (or Ish-chai), an Israelite -- a valiant man. see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh see HEBREW (H2428) chayil see HEBREW (H2416) chay

column7: men of Tob, inhab. of a region East of the Jordan
column9: From (H376) 'iysh and (H2897) Towb; man of Tob; Ish-Tob, a place in Palestine -- Ish-tob. see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh see HEBREW (H2897) Towb

column8: art thou, can, do ye, have, it be, there is are, we will not
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H3426) yesh; properly, entity; used only as a particle of affirmation, there is -- art thou, can, do ye, have, it be, there is (are), X we will not. see HEBREW (H3426) yesh

column7: with me is God, an Israelite name
column9: Perhaps from (H837) 'osher and (H410) 'el; God has arrived; Ithiel, the name of an Israelite, also of a symbolical person -- Ithiel. see HEBREW (H837) 'osher see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: land of palms, a son of Aaron
column9: From (H339) 'iy and (H8558) tamar; coast of the palm-tree; Ithamar, a son of Aaron -- Ithamar. see HEBREW (H339) 'iy see HEBREW (H8558) tamar
Or (shortened) ethan {ay-thawn'}; from an unused root (meaning to continue); permanence; hence (concrete) permanent; specifically a chieftain -- hard, mighty, rough, strength, strong.
The same as (H386) 'eythan; permanent; Ethan, the name of four Israelites -- Ethan. see HEBREW (H386) 'eythan

column7: (month of) "steady flowings", the seventh month in the Jewish calendar
column9: Plural of (H386) 'eythan; always with the article; the permanent brooks; Ethanim, the name of a month -- Ethanim. see HEBREW (H386) 'eythan

column8: also, in any wise, at least, but, certainly, even, howbeit, nevertheless,
column9: Akin to (H403) 'aken; a particle of affirmation, surely; hence (by limitation) only -- also, in any wise, at least, but, certainly, even, howbeit, nevertheless, notwithstanding, only, save, surely, of a surety, truly, verily, + wherefore, yet (but). see HEBREW (H403) 'aken

column7: the name of a city in N. Bab
column9: From an unused root probably meaning to strengthen; a fortress; Accad, a place in Babylon -- Accad.
From (H3576) kazab; falsehood; by implication treachery -- liar, lie. see HEBREW (H3576) kazab
From (H391) 'akzab; deceitful (in the sense of a winter- torrent which fails in summer); Akzib, the name of two places in Palestine -- Achzib. see HEBREW (H391) 'akzab
From an unused root (apparently meaning to act harshly); violent; by implication deadly; also (in a good sense) brave -- cruel, fierce.
From (H393) 'akzar; terrible -- cruel (one). see HEBREW (H393) 'akzar
From (H394) 'akzariy; fierceness -- cruel. see HEBREW (H394) 'akzariy
Feminine from (H398) 'akal; something eatable, i.e. Food -- meat. see HEBREW (H398) 'akal
Of uncertain derivation; Akish, a Philistine king -- Achish.

column8: burn up, consume, devourer, up, dine, eater, up,
column9: A primitive root; to eat (literally or figuratively) -- X at all, burn up, consume, devour(-er, up), dine, eat(-er, up), feed (with), food, X freely, X in...wise(-deed, plenty), (lay) meat, X quite.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H398) 'akal -- + accuse, devour, eat. see HEBREW (H398) 'akal

column8: eating, food, mealtime, meat, prey, victuals
column9: From (H398) 'akal; food -- eating, food, meal(-time), meat, prey, victuals. see HEBREW (H398) 'akal
Or mukkal {ook-kawl'}; apparently from (H398) 'akal; devoured; Ucal, a fancy name -- Ucal. see HEBREW (H398) 'akal
Feminine of (H401) 'Ukal; food -- consume, devour, eat, food, meat. see HEBREW (H401) 'Ukal

column8: but, certainly, nevertheless, surely, truly, verily
column9: From (H3559) kuwn (compare (H3651) ken); firmly; figuratively, surely; also (advers.) But -- but, certainly, nevertheless, surely, truly, verily. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn see HEBREW (H3651) ken
A primitive root; apparently meaning to curve (as with a burden); to urge -- crave.
From (H404) 'akaph; a load; by implication, a stroke (others dignity) -- hand. see HEBREW (H404) 'akaph
From an unused root meaning to dig; a farmer -- husbandman, ploughman.
From (H3784) kashaph; fascination; Acshaph, a place in Palestine -- Achshaph. see HEBREW (H3784) kashaph

column8: nay, neither, never, no, nor, not, nothing, rather than
column9: A negative particle (akin to (H3808) lo'); not (the qualified negation, used as a deprecative); once (Job 24:25) as a noun, nothing -- nay, neither, + never, no,nor, not, nothing (worth), rather than. see HEBREW (H3808) lo'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H408) 'al -- not. see HEBREW (H408) 'al

column8: God, goodly, great, idol, mighty one, power, strong
column9: Shortened from (H352) 'ayil; strength; as adjective, mighty; especially the Almighty (but used also of any deity) -- God (god), X goodly, X great, idol, might(-y one), power, strong. Compare names in \"-el.\" see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil
A demonstrative particle (but only in a plural sense) these or those -- these, those. Compare (H428) 'el-leh. see HEBREW (H428) 'el-leh
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H411) 'el -- these. see HEBREW (H411) 'el

column8: about, according to, after, against, among, as for, at, because, before both
column9: (but only used in the shortened constructive form sel {el}); a primitive particle; properly, denoting motion towards, but occasionally used of a quiescent position, i.e. Near, with or among; often in general, to -- about, according to,after, against, among, as for, at, because(-fore, -side), both...and, by, concerning, for, from, X hath, in(- to), near, (out) of, over, through, to(-ward), under, unto, upon, whether, with(-in).
A variation of (H424) 'elah; oak; Ela, an Israelite -- Elah. see HEBREW (H424) 'elah

column7: the mighty God of Israel, an altar of Jacob
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H430) 'elohiym and (H3478) Yisra'el; the mighty god if Jisrael; El-Elohi-Jisrael, the title given to a consecrated spot by Jacob -- El-elohe-israel. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H430) 'elohiym see HEBREW (H3478) Yisra'el

column7: the God of Bethel, an altar of Jacob
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H1008) Beyth-'El; the God of Bethel; El-Bethel, the title given to a consecrated spot by Jacob -- El-beth-el. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H1008) Beyth-'El
From (H410) 'el and (H1378) gabiysh; hail (as if a great pearl) -- great hail(-stones). see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H1378) gabiysh
By transposition for (H484) 'almuggiym; sticks of algum wood -- algum (trees). see HEBREW (H484) 'almuggiym

column7: God has loved, an Israelite name
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H1730) dowd; God has loved; Eldad, an Israelite -- Eldad. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H1730) dowd

column7: God has called, a son of Midian
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H3045) yada'; God of knowledge; Eldaah, a son of Midian -- Eldaah. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3045) yada'
A primitive root (rather identical with (H422) 'alah through the idea of invocation); to bewail -- lament. see HEBREW (H422) 'alah
A primitive root; properly, to adjure, i.e. (usually in a bad sense) imprecate -- adjure, curse, swear.
From (H422) 'alah; an imprecation -- curse, cursing, execration, oath, swearing. see HEBREW (H422) 'alah
Feminine of (H352) 'ayil; an oak or other strong tree -- elm, oak, teil-tree. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil

column7: terebinth, an Israelite name, also an Edomite name
column9: The same as (H424) 'elah; Elah, the name of an Edomite, of four Israelites, and also of a place in Palestine -- Elah. see HEBREW (H424) 'elah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H433) 'elowahh; God -- God, god. see HEBREW (H433) 'elowahh
A variation of (H424) 'elah -- oak. see HEBREW (H424) 'elah

column8: another; one sort, so, some, such, them, these same, they, this,
column9: Prolonged from (H411) 'el; these or those -- an- (the) other; one sort, so, some, such, them, these (same), they, this, those, thus, which, who(-m). see HEBREW (H411) 'el
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H428) 'el-leh -- these. see HEBREW (H428) 'el-leh

column8: angels, exceeding, God, very great, mighty
column9: Plural of (H433) 'elowahh; gods in the ordinary sense; but specifically used (in the plural thus, especially with the article) of the supreme God; occasionally applied by way of deference to magistrates; and sometimes as a superlative -- angels, X exceeding, God (gods)(-dess, -ly), X (very) great, judges, X mighty. see HEBREW (H433) 'elowahh
(Aramaic) probably prolonged from (H412) 'el; lo! -- behold. see HEBREW (H412) 'el
Probably from (H408) 'al; nay, i.e. (softened) if -- but if, yea though. see HEBREW (H408) 'al
Probably prolonged (emphat.) From (H410) 'el; a deity or the Deity -- God, god. See (H430) 'elohiym. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H430) 'elohiym
For (H457) 'eliyl; good for nothing -- thing of nought. see HEBREW (H457) 'eliyl
Probably of foreign derivation; Elul, the sixth Jewish month -- Elul.
Prolonged from (H352) 'ayil; an oak or other strong tree -- plain. See also (H356) 'Eylown. see HEBREW (H352) 'ayil see HEBREW (H356) 'Eylown
A variation of (H436) 'elown -- oak. see HEBREW (H436) 'elown
The same as (H437) 'allown; Allon, an Israelite, also a place in Palestine -- Allon. see HEBREW (H437) 'allown

column7: oak of weeping, a tree near the grave of Rebekah\'s nurse
column9: From (H437) 'allown and a variation of (H1068) bkiyth; oak of weeping; Allon-Bakuth, a monumental tree -- Allon-bachuth. see HEBREW (H437) 'allown see HEBREW (H1068) bkiyth
Or rather (shortened) oeloniy {ay-lo-nee'}; patron from (H438) 'Allown; an Elonite or descendant (collectively) of Elon -- Elonites. see HEBREW (H438) 'Allown

column8: captain, duke, chief friend, governor, guide, ox
column9: Or (shortened) talluph {al-loof'}; from (H502) 'alph; familiar; a friend, also gentle; hence, a bullock (as being tame; applied, although masculine, to a cow); and so, a chieftain (as notable, like neat cattle) -- captain, duke, (chief) friend, governor, guide, ox. see HEBREW (H502) 'alph
Of uncertain derivation; Alush, a place in the Desert -- Alush.
From (H410) 'el and (H2064) zabad; God has bestowed; Elzabad, the name of two Israelites -- Elzabad. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H2064) zabad
A primitive root; to muddle, i.e. (figuratively and intransitive) to turn (morally) corrupt -- become filthy.

column7: God has been gracious, two of David\'s leaders
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H2603) chanan; God (is) gracious; Elchanan, an Israelite -- Elkanan. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H2603) chanan

column7: God is father, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H1) 'ab; God of (his) father; Eliab, the name of six Israelites -- Eliab. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H1) 'ab

column7: my God is God, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H410) 'el repeated; God of (his) God; Eliel, the name of nine Israelites -- Eliel. see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or (contraction);Eliyathah {el-ee-yaw- thaw'}; from (H410) 'el and (H225) 'uwth; God of (his) consent; Eliathah, an Israelite -- Eliathah. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H225) 'uwth

column7: God has loved, an Israelite name
column9: From the same as (H419) 'Eldad; God of (his) love; Elidad, an Israelite -- Elidad. see HEBREW (H419) 'Eldad
From (H410) 'el and (H3045) yada'; God (is) knowing; Eljada, the name of two Israelites and of an Aramaean leader -- Eliada. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3045) yada'
From (H422) 'alah (in the original sense of strength); the stout part, i.e. The fat tail of the Oriental sheep -- rump. see HEBREW (H422) 'alah

column7: Yah is God, a well-known prophet of Isr., also three other Isr
column9: Or prolonged teliyahuw {ay-lee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H410) 'el and (H3050) Yahh; God of Jehovah; Elijah, the name of the famous prophet and of two other Israelites -- Elijah, Eliah. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

Or (fully) deliyhuwh {el-ee-hoo'}; from (H410) 'el and (H1931) huw'; God of him; Elihu, the name of one of Job's friends, and of three Israelites -- Elihu. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H1931) huw'

column7: toward Yah (are) my eyes, two Israelites
column9: Or (shortened) yelyow{eynay {el- yo-ay-nah'ee}; from (H413) 'el and (H3068) Yhovah and (H5869) ayin; towards Jehovah (are) my eyes; Eljehoenai or Eljoenai, the name of seven Israelites -- Elihoenai, Elionai. see HEBREW (H413) 'el see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H5869) ayin

column7: God hides, one of David\'s leaders
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H2244) chaba'; God will hide; Eljachba, an Israelite -- Eliahbah. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H2244) chaba'

column7: God of autumn, one of Solomon\'s scribes
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H2779) choreph; God of autumn; Elichoreph, an Israelite -- Elihoreph. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H2779) choreph

column8: idol, no value, thing of nothing
column9: Apparently from (H408) 'al; good for nothing, by anal. Vain or vanity; specifically an idol -- idol, no value, thing of nought. see HEBREW (H408) 'al

column7: God is king, the husband of Naomi
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H4428) melek; God of (the) king; Elimelek, an Israelite -- Elimelech. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H4428) melek
(Aramaic) or shorter oillen {il-lane'}; prolonged from (H412) 'el; these -- the, these. see HEBREW (H412) 'el
From (H410) 'el and (H3254) yacaph; God (is) gatherer; Eljasaph, the name of two Israelites -- Eliasaph. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3254) yacaph

column7: God is help, the name of several Israelites, also of a Damascene
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H5828) ezer; God of help; Eliezer, the name of a Damascene and of ten Israelites -- Eliezer. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5828) ezer
Probably contracted for (H454) Elyhow'eynay; Elienai, an Israelite -- Elienai. see HEBREW (H454) Elyhow'eynay

column7: God is kinsman, an Israelite name
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H5971) am; God of (the) people; Eliam, an Israelite -- Eliam. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5971) am

column7: God is fine gold, a son of Esau, also a friend of Job
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H6337) paz; God of gold; Eliphaz, the name of one of Job's friends, and of a son of Esau -- Eliphaz. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6337) paz

column7: God has judged, one of David\'s heroes
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H6419) palal; God of judgment; Eliphal, an Israelite -- Eliphal. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6419) palal

column7: may God distinguish him, a doorkeeper
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H6395) palah; God of his distinction; Eliphelehu, an Israelite -- Elipheleh. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6395) palah

column7: God is deliverance, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or (shortened) Elpelet {el-peh'-let}; from (H410) 'el and (H6405) pallet; God of deliverance; Eliphelet or Elpelet, the name of six Israelites -- Eliphalet, Eliphelet, Elpalet. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6405) pallet

column7: God of (the) rock, a Reubenite leader
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H6697) tsuwr; God of (the) rock; Elitsur, an Israelite -- Elizur. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6697) tsuwr

Or (shortened) Eltsaphan {el-tsaw- fawn'}; from (H410) 'el and (H6845) tsaphan; God of treasure; Elitsaphan or Eltsaphan, an Israelite -- Elizaphan, Elzaphan. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6845) tsaphan

column7: God of rejection, one of David\'s heroes
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H6958) qow'; God of rejection; Elika, an Israelite -- Elika. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6958) qow'
From (H410) 'el and (H6965) quwm; God of raising; Eljakim, the name of four Israelites -- Eliakim. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6965) quwm

column7: God is an oath, the wife of Aaron
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H7651) sheba' (in the sense of (H7650) shaba'); God of (the) oath; Elisheba, the wife of Aaron -- Elisheba. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H7651) sheba' see HEBREW (H7650) shaba'

column7: a son of Javan, also his desc. and their land
column9: Probably of foreign derivation; Elishah, a son of Javan -- Elishah.

column7: God is salvation, a son of David
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H7769) shuwa'; God of supplication (or of riches); Elishua, the son of King David -- Elishua. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H7769) shuwa'

column7: God restores, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H7725) shuwb; God will restore; Eljashib, the name of six Israelites -- Eliashib. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb

column7: God has heard, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H8085) shama'; God of hearing; Elishama, the name of seven Israelites -- Elishama. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H8085) shama'

column7: God is salvation, a well-known Israelite prophet
column9: Contracted for (H474) Eliyshuwa'.; Elisha, the famous prophet -- Elisha. see HEBREW (H474) Eliyshuwa'
From (H410) 'el and (H8199) shaphat; God of judgment; Elishaphat, an Israelite -- Elishaphat. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H8199) shaphat
(Aramaic) prolonged from (H412) 'el; these -- these, those. see HEBREW (H412) 'el
By reduplication from (H421) 'alah; alas! -- woe. see HEBREW (H421) 'alah

column8: bind, be dumb, put to silence
column9: A primitive root; to tie fast; hence (of the mouth) to be tongue-tied -- bind, be dumb, put to silence.
From (H481) 'alam; silence (i.e. Mute justice) -- congregation. Compare (H3128) yownath 'elem rchoqiym. see HEBREW (H481) 'alam see HEBREW (H3128) yownath 'elem rchoqiym
From (H481) 'alam; speechless -- dumb (man). see HEBREW (H481) 'alam
Probably of foreign derivation (used thus only in the plural); almug (i.e. Probably sandle-wood) sticks -- almug trees. Compare (H418) 'alguwmmiym. see HEBREW (H418) 'alguwmmiym
Or (masculine) ealum {aw-loom'}; passive participle of (H481) 'alam; something bound; a sheaf -- sheaf. see HEBREW (H481) 'alam

column7: a son of Joktan, also his desc
column9: Probably of foreign derivation -- Almodad, a son of Joktan -- Almodad.

column7: an oak of (the) king, a place in Asher
column9: From (H427) 'allah and (H4428) melek; oak of (the) king; Allammelek, a place in Palestine -- Alammelech. see HEBREW (H427) 'allah see HEBREW (H4428) melek
Prolonged from (H481) 'alam in the sense of bereavement; discarded (as a divorced person) -- forsaken. see HEBREW (H481) 'alam
From (H481) 'alam as in (H488) 'alman; bereavement -- widowhood. see HEBREW (H481) 'alam see HEBREW (H488) 'alman
Fem of (H488) 'alman; a widow; also a desolate place -- desolate house (palace), widow. see HEBREW (H488) 'alman
Feminine of (H488) 'alman; concrete, a widow; abstract, widowhood -- widow, widowhood. see HEBREW (H488) 'alman
From (H489) 'almon in the sense of concealment; some one (i.e. So and so, without giving the name of the person or place) -- one, and such. see HEBREW (H489) 'almon

column7: God is pleasantness, the father of two of David\'s heroes
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H5276) na'em; God (is his) delight; Elnaam, an Israelite -- Elnaam. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5276) na'em

column7: God has given, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H5414) nathan; God (is the) giver; Elnathan, the name of four Israelites -- Elnathan. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5414) nathan
Probably of foreign derivation; Ellasar, an early country of Asia -- Ellasar.
From (H410) 'el and (H5749) uwd; God has testified; Elad, an Israelite -- Elead. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5749) uwd
From (H410) 'el and (H5710) adah; God has decked; Eladah, an Israelite -- Eladah. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5710) adah

column7: God is my strength, one of David\'s heroes
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H5756) uwz (in the sense of (H5797) oz); God (is) defensive; Eluzai, an Israelite -- Eluzai. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5756) uwz see HEBREW (H5797) oz
From (H410) 'el and (H5826) azar; God (is) helper; Elazar, the name of seven Israelites -- Eleazar. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5826) azar
Or (more properly) gel aleh {el-aw-lay'}; from (H410) 'el and (H5927) alah; God (is) going up; Elale or Elaleh, a place east of the Jordan -- Elealeh. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H5927) alah

column7: God has made, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H6213) asah; God has made; Elasah, the name of four Israelites -- Elasah, Eleasah. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6213) asah
A primitive root, to associate with; hence, to learn (and causatively to teach) -- learn, teach, utter.
Denominative from (H505) 'eleph; causative, to make a thousandfold -- bring forth thousands. see HEBREW (H505) 'eleph
From (H502) 'alph; a family; also (from the sense of yoking or taming) an ox or cow -- family, kine, oxen. see HEBREW (H502) 'alph
Prop, the same as (H504) 'eleph; hence (the ox's head being the first letter of the alphabet, and this eventually used as a numeral) a thousand -- thousand. see HEBREW (H504) 'eleph
(Aramaic) or meleph (Aramaic) {eh'-lef}; corresponding to (H505) 'eleph -- thousand. see HEBREW (H505) 'eleph
The same as (H505) 'eleph; Eleph, a place in Palestine -- Eleph. see HEBREW (H505) 'eleph
From (H410) 'el and (H6466) pa'al; God (is) act; Elpaal, an Israelite -- Elpaal. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6466) pa'al
A primitive root; to press -- urge.
Probably from (H408) 'al and (H6965) quwm; a non-rising (i.e. Resistlessness) -- no rising up. see HEBREW (H408) 'al see HEBREW (H6965) quwm

column7: God has created, or "God has taken possession", the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H410) 'el and (H7069) qanah; God has obtained; Elkanah, the name of several Israelites -- Elkanah. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H7069) qanah
Patrial from a name of uncertain derivation; an Elkoshite or native of Elkosh -- Elkoshite.

column7: God is generator, a city in S. Judah
column9: Probably from (H410) 'el and a masculine form of (H8435) towldah (compare (H8434) Towlad); God (is) generator; Eltolad, a place in Palestine -- Eltolad. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H8435) towldah see HEBREW (H8434) Towlad
Or (more properly) neltqeh {el-te-kay'}; of uncertain derivation; Eltekeh or Elteke, a place in Palestine -- Eltekeh.
From (H410) 'el and (H8626) taqan; God (is) straight; Eltekon, a place in Palestine -- Eltekon. see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H8626) taqan

column7: destroy not, a phrase in Psalm titles
column9: From (H408) 'al and (H7843) shachath; Thou must not destroy; probably the opening words to a popular song -- Al-taschith. see HEBREW (H408) 'al see HEBREW (H7843) shachath
A primitive word; a mother (as the bond of the family); in a wide sense (both literally and figuratively (like (H1) 'ab) -- dam, mother, X parting. see HEBREW (H1) 'ab

column4: conjunction; hypothetical particle; imperfect; infinitive; interrogative particle
column9: A primitive particle; used very widely as demonstrative, lo!; interrog., whether?; or conditional, if, although; also Oh that!, when; hence, as a negative, not -- (and, can-, doubtless, if, that) (not), + but, either, + except, + more(-over if, than), neither, nevertheless, nor, oh that, or, + save (only, -ing), seeing, since, sith, + surely (no more, none, not), though, + of a truth, + unless, + verily, when, whereas, whether, while, + yet.
Apparently a primitive word; a maid-servant or female slave -- (hand-)bondmaid(-woman), maid(-servant).

Prolonged from (H517) 'em; properly, a mother (i.e. Unit of measure, or the fore-arm (below the elbow), i.e. A cubit; also a door-base (as a bond of the entrance) -- cubit, + hundred (by exchange for (H3967) me'ah), measure, post. see HEBREW (H517) 'em see HEBREW (H3967) me'ah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H520) 'ammah -- cubit. see HEBREW (H520) 'ammah
The same as (H520) 'ammah; Ammah, a hill in Palestine -- Ammah. see HEBREW (H520) 'ammah
From the same as (H517) 'em; a collection, i.e. Community of persons -- nation, people. see HEBREW (H517) 'em
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H523) 'ummah -- nation. see HEBREW (H523) 'ummah
From (H539) 'aman, probably in the sense of training; skilled, i.e. An architect (like (H542) 'aman) -- one brought up. see HEBREW (H539) 'aman see HEBREW (H542) 'aman
The same as (H525) 'amown; Amon, the name of three Israelites -- Amon. see HEBREW (H525) 'amown
A variation for (H1995) hamown; a throng of people -- multitude. see HEBREW (H1995) hamown
Of Egyptian derivation; Amon (i.e. Ammon or Amn), a deity of Egypt (used only as an adjunct of (H4996) No') -- multitude, populous. see HEBREW (H4996) No'
From (H539) 'aman; established, i.e. (figuratively) trusty; also (abstractly) trustworthiness -- faith(-ful), truth. see HEBREW (H539) 'aman

column8: faithful set office, stability, steady, truly, truth, verily
column9: ); or (shortened) >emunah {em-oo-naw'} feminine of (H529) 'emuwn; literally firmness; figuratively security; morally fidelity -- faith(-ful, -ly, -ness, (man)), set office, stability, steady, truly, truth, verily. see HEBREW (H529) 'emuwn
From (H553) 'amats; strong; Amots, an Israelite -- Amoz. see HEBREW (H553) 'amats
An abbrev. For (H526) 'Amown; Ami, an Israelite -- Ami. see HEBREW (H526) 'Amown
Or (shortened) ammits {am-meets'}; from (H553) 'amats; strong or (abstractly) strength -- courageous, mighty, strong (one). see HEBREW (H553) 'amats
Apparently from (H559) 'amar (in the sense of self- exaltation); a summit (of a tree or mountain -- bough, branch. see HEBREW (H559) 'amar
A primitive root; to droop; by implication to be sick, to mourn -- languish, be weak, wax feeble.
From (H535) 'amal; sick -- weak. see HEBREW (H535) 'amal
From (H535) 'amal; languid -- feeble. see HEBREW (H535) 'amal
From (H517) 'em; gathering-spot; Amam, a place in Palestine -- Amam. see HEBREW (H517) 'em

column8: hence, assurance, believe, bring up, establish, steadfast,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to build up or support; to foster as a parent or nurse; figuratively to render (or be) firm or faithful, to trust or believe, to be permanent or quiet; morally to be true or certain; once (Isa. 30:21; interchangeable with (H541) 'aman) to go to the right hand -- hence, assurance, believe, bring up, establish, + fail, be faithful (of long continuance, stedfast, sure, surely, trusty, verified), nurse, (-ing father), (put), trust, turn to the right. see HEBREW (H541) 'aman
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H539) 'aman -- believe, faithful, sure. see HEBREW (H539) 'aman
Denominative from (H3225) yamiyn; to take the right hand road -- turn to the right. See (H539) 'aman. see HEBREW (H3225) yamiyn see HEBREW (H539) 'aman
From (H539) 'aman (in the sense of training); an expert -- cunning workman. see HEBREW (H539) 'aman
From (H539) 'aman; sure; abstract, faithfulness; adverb, truly -- Amen, so be it, truth. see HEBREW (H539) 'aman
From (H539) 'aman; verity -- truth. see HEBREW (H539) 'aman
Feminine of (H544) 'omen (in the specific sense of training); tutelage -- brought up. see HEBREW (H544) 'omen
Feminine form of (H544) 'omen (in its usual sense); adverb, surely -- indeed. see HEBREW (H544) 'omen
Feminine active participle of (H544) 'omen (in the original sense of supporting); a column -- pillar. see HEBREW (H544) 'omen
Feminine of (H543) 'amen; something fixed, i.e. A covenant. An allowance -- certain portion, sure. see HEBREW (H543) 'amen

column7: a river near Damascus, also the region from which it flows
column9: The same as (H548) 'amanah; Amanah, a mountain near Damascus -- Amana. see HEBREW (H548) 'amanah
Or uamiynown {am-ee-nohn'}; from (H539) 'aman; faithful; Amnon (or Aminon), a son of David -- Amnon. see HEBREW (H539) 'aman

column8: indeed, no doubt, surely, it is
column9: Adverb from (H544) 'omen; verily -- indeed, no doubt, surely, (it is, of a) true(-ly, -th). see HEBREW (H544) 'omen
An orthographical variation of (H551) 'omnam -- in (very) deed; of a surety. see HEBREW (H551) 'omnam

column7: to be stout, strong, bold, alert
column8: confirm, be courageous of good courage, steadfastly minded, strong, stronger, establish, fortify, harden,
column9: A primitive root; to be alert, physically (on foot) or mentally (in courage) -- confirm, be courageous (of good courage, stedfastly minded, strong, stronger), establish, fortify, harden, increase, prevail, strengthen (self), make strong (obstinate, speed).
Probably from (H553) 'amats; of a strong color, i.e. Red (others fleet) -- bay. see HEBREW (H553) 'amats
From (H553) 'amats; strength -- stronger. see HEBREW (H553) 'amats
From (H553) 'amats; force -- strength. see HEBREW (H553) 'amats
From (H553) 'amats; strong; Amtsi, an Israelite -- Amzi. see HEBREW (H553) 'amats

column7: Yah is mighty, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or mamatsyahuw {am-ats-yaw'-hoo}; from (H553) 'amats and (H3050) Yahh; strength of Jah; Amatsjah, the name of four Israelites -- Amaziah. see HEBREW (H553) 'amats see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column8: answer, appoint, avouch, bid, boast self, call, certify, challenge,
column9: A primitive root; to say (used with great latitude) -- answer, appoint, avouch, bid, boast self, call, certify, challenge, charge, + (at the, give) command(-ment), commune, consider, declare, demand, X desire, determine, X expressly, X indeed, X intend, name, X plainly, promise, publish, report, require, say, speak (against, of), X still, X suppose, talk, tell, term, X that is, X think, use (speech), utter, X verily, X yet.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H559) 'amar -- command, declare, say, speak, tell. see HEBREW (H559) 'amar

column8: answer, appointed unto him, saying, speech, word
column9: From (H559) 'amar; something said -- answer, X appointed unto him, saying, speech, word. see HEBREW (H559) 'amar
The same as (H561) 'emer -- promise, speech, thing, word. see HEBREW (H561) 'emer
(Aramaic) perhaps from (H560) 'amar (in the sense of bringing forth); a lamb -- lamb. see HEBREW (H560) 'amar

column7: the name of several Israelites, perhaps also a place in Babylon
column9: From (H559) 'amar; talkative; Immer, the name of five Israelites -- Immer. see HEBREW (H559) 'amar
Or memrah {em-raw'}; feminine of (H561) 'emer, and meaning the same -- commandment, speech, word. see HEBREW (H561) 'emer
From (H564) 'Immer; wordy; Imri, the name of two Israelites -- Imri. see HEBREW (H564) 'Immer

Probably a patronymic from an unused name derived from (H559) 'amar in the sense of publicity, i.e. Prominence; thus, a mountaineer; an Emorite, one of the Canaanitish tribes -- Amorite. see HEBREW (H559) 'amar

column7: Yah has promised, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or prolonged tamaryahuw {am-ar-yaw'-hoo}; from (H559) 'amar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has said (i.e. Promised); Amarjah, the name of nine Israelites -- Amariah. see HEBREW (H559) 'amar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Of uncertain (perhaps foreign) derivation; Amraphel, a king of Shinar -- Amraphel.
Time past, i.e. Yesterday or last night -- former time, yesterday(-night)

column8: assuredly, establishment, faithful, right, sure, true, verity
column9: Contracted from (H539) 'aman; stability; (figuratively) certainty, truth, trustworthiness -- assured(-ly), establishment, faithful, right, sure, true (-ly, -th), verity. see HEBREW (H539) 'aman
From (H4969) mathach; properly, something expansive, i.e. A bag -- sack. see HEBREW (H4969) mathach
From (H571) 'emeth; veracious; Amittai, an Israelite -- Amittai. see HEBREW (H571) 'emeth
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of (H4975) mothen; well-loined (i.e. Burly) or mighty -- terrible. see HEBREW (H4975) mothen

column8: any no whither, now, where, whithersoever
column9: Or manah {aw-naw'}; contracted from (H370) 'aiyn; where?; hence, whither?, when?; also hither and thither -- + any (no) whither, now, where, whither(-soever). see HEBREW (H370) 'aiyn
(Aramaic) or.anah (Aramaic) {an-aw'}; corresponding to (H589) 'aniy; I -- I, as for me. see HEBREW (H589) 'aniy
Or mannah {awn-naw'}; apparent contracted from (H160) 'ahabah and (H4994) na'; oh now! -- I (me) beseech (pray) thee, O. see HEBREW (H160) 'ahabah see HEBREW (H4994) na'
A primitive root; to groan -- lament, mourn.

column7: to be opportune, to meet, encounter opportunely
column8: befall, deliver, happen, seek a quarrel
column9: A primitive root (perhaps rather identical with (H578) 'anah through the idea of contraction in anguish); to approach; hence, to meet in various senses -- befall, deliver, happen, seek a quarrel. see HEBREW (H578) 'anah
Contracted for (H587) 'anachnuw; we -- we. see HEBREW (H587) 'anachnuw
(Aramaic) or (feminine) inniyn (Aramaic) {in- neen'}; corresponding to (H1992) hem; they -- X are, them, these. see HEBREW (H1992) hem

column8: another, bloodthirsty, certain, divers, fellow, in the flower of their age
column9: From (H605) 'anash; properly, a mortal (and thus differing from the more dignified (H120) 'adam); hence, a man in general (singly or collectively) -- another, X (blood-)thirsty, certain, chap(-man); divers, fellow, X in the flower of their age, husband, (certain, mortal) man, people, person, servant, some (X of them), + stranger, those, + their trade. It is often unexpressed in the English versions, especially when used in apposition with another word. Compare (H376) 'iysh. see HEBREW (H605) 'anash see HEBREW (H120) 'adam see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh
The same as (H582) 'enowsh; Enosh, a son of Seth; --Enos. see HEBREW (H582) 'enowsh
A primitive root; to sigh -- groan, mourn, sigh.
From (H585) 'anachah; sighing -- groaning, mourn, sigh. see HEBREW (H585) 'anachah
(Aramaic) or ganachnah (Aramaic) {an-akh- naw'}; corresponding to (H587) 'anachnuw; we -- we. see HEBREW (H587) 'anachnuw
Apparently from (H595) 'anokiy; we -- ourselves, us, we. see HEBREW (H595) 'anokiy
Probably from the same root as (H5170) nachar; a gorge or narrow pass; Anacharath, a place in Palestine -- Anaharath. see HEBREW (H5170) nachar

column8: I, as for me, mine, myself, we, which, who
column9: Contracted from (H595) 'anokiy; I -- I, (as for) me, mine, myself, we, X which, X who. see HEBREW (H595) 'anokiy
Probably from (H579) 'anah (in the sense of conveyance); -a ship or (collectively)a fleet -- galley, navy (of ships). see HEBREW (H579) 'anah
Feminine of (H590) 'oniy; a ship -- ship((-men)). see HEBREW (H590) 'oniy
From (H578) 'anah; groaning -- lamentation, sorrow. see HEBREW (H578) 'anah

column7: lament of people, an Israelite name
column9: From (H578) 'anah and (H5971) am; groaning of (the) people; Aniam, an Israelite -- Aniam. see HEBREW (H578) 'anah see HEBREW (H5971) am
Probably from an unused root meaning to be narrow; according to most a plumb-line, and to others a hook -- plumb-line.
Sometimes {aw-no'-kee}; a primitive pro.; I -- I, me, X which.
A primitive root; to mourn, i.e. Complain -- complain.
To insist -- compel.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H597) 'anac; figuratively, to distress -- trouble. see HEBREW (H597) 'anac
A primitive root; to breathe hard, i.e. Be enraged -- be angry (displeased).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H639) 'aph (only in the plural as a singular); the face -- face, visage. see HEBREW (H639) 'aph
From (H599) 'anaph; an unclean bird, perhaps the parrot (from its irascibility) -- heron. see HEBREW (H599) 'anaph
A primitive root; to shriek -- cry, groan.
From (H602) 'anaq; shrieking -- crying out, groaning, sighing. see HEBREW (H602) 'anaq
The same as (H603) 'anaqah; some kind of lizard, probably the gecko (from its wail) -- ferret. see HEBREW (H603) 'anaqah
A primitive root; to be frail, feeble, or (figuratively) melancholy -- desperate(-ly wicked), incurable, sick, woeful.
(Aramaic) or renash (Aramaic) {en-ash'}; corresponding to (H582) 'enowsh; a man -- man, + whosoever. see HEBREW (H582) 'enowsh
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H859) 'attah; thou -- as for thee, thou. see HEBREW (H859) 'attah
(Aramaic) plural of (H607) 'antah; ye -- ye. see HEBREW (H607) 'antah
Of uncertain derivation; Asa, the name of a king and of a Levite -- Asa.
From (H5480) cuwk; anointed, i.e. An oil-flask -- pot. see HEBREW (H5480) cuwk
Of uncertain derivation; hurt -- mischief.
From (H631) 'acar; a bond (especially manacles of a prisoner) -- band, + prison. see HEBREW (H631) 'acar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H612) 'ecuwr -- band, imprisonment. see HEBREW (H612) 'ecuwr
Or maciph {aw-seef'}; from (H622) 'acaph; gathered, i.e. (abstractly) a gathering in of crops -- ingathering. see HEBREW (H622) 'acaph
From (H631) 'acar; bound, i.e. A captive -- (those which are) bound, prisoner. see HEBREW (H631) 'acar
For (H615) 'aciyr: prisoner. see HEBREW (H615) 'aciyr
The same as (H616) 'acciyr; prisoner; Assir, the name of two Israelites -- Assir. see HEBREW (H616) 'acciyr
From an unused root meaning to heap together; a storehouse (only in the plural) -- barn, storehouse.
Of uncertain derivation; Asnah, one of the Nethinim -- Asnah.
Of foreign derivation; Osnappar, an Assyrian king -- Asnapper.

column7: perhaps "belonging to Neith", the wife of Joseph
column9: Of Egyptian derivation; Asenath, the wife of Joseph -- Asenath.

column8: assemble, bring, consume, destroy, fetch, gather in, together, up again,
column9: A primitive root; to gather for any purpose; hence, to receive, take away, i.e. Remove (destroy, leave behind, put up, restore, etc.) -- assemble, bring, consume, destroy, felch, gather (in, together, up again), X generally, get (him), lose, put all together, receive, recover (another from leprosy), (be) rereward, X surely, take (away, into, up), X utterly, withdraw.

column7: gatherer, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H622) 'acaph; collector; Asaph, the name of three Israelites, and of the family of the first -- Asaph. see HEBREW (H622) 'acaph

column7: a store (i.e. a supply of provisions)
column9: Passive participle of (H622) 'acaph; collected (only in the plural), i.e. A collection of offerings) -- threshold, Asuppim. see HEBREW (H622) 'acaph
From (H622) 'acaph; a collection (of fruits) -- gathering. see HEBREW (H622) 'acaph
From (H622) 'acaph; a collection of people (only adverbial) -- X together. see HEBREW (H622) 'acaph
Fem of (H624) 'acuph.; a collection of (learned) men (only in the plural) -- assembly. see HEBREW (H624) 'acuph
By reduplication from (H624) 'acuph; gathered up together, i.e. A promiscuous assemblage (of people) -- mixt multitude. see HEBREW (H624) 'acuph
(Aramaic) of Persian derivation; diligently -- fast, forthwith, speed(-ily).
